description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Possible relocation package up to £8k&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to develop your nursing skills in the specialist areas of eating disorders and perinatal mental health?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to be part of our exciting 18 month nursing rotation programme?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Are you ready to make that move to live and work in beautiful Devon?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are searching for motivated and innovative qualified professionals to join our 18 month rotation inpatient programme. You will spend nine months on a ward, operating on a 24/7 shift basis, in the following units in Exeter:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Haldon Eating Disorder Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jasmine Lodge Mother and Baby Unit (MBU)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will qualify for unsocial enhancements in addition to your basic pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open to Registered Nurses (mental health), newly qualified and those recently retired or thinking about returning to practice. You do not need to have had experience of working in these specialties to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: 27 and 30 October&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the end of the rotation we will offer you a substantive role within one of these units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an incredible opportunity to establish a career, where you will be well supported, with dedicated supervision and encouraged to develop your clinical skills within a stimulating learning environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll become part of a multi-disciplinary team (MDT), using your skills and experience to design a package of care for people, who with your help can improve their mental health, recover independence and return to their local community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are newly qualified and want to develop your career or an experienced health professional who is looking for a new challenge, we welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have excellent communication skills, a commitment to working flexibly and a passion to wanting to make a difference to people’s lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have no preconceptions about the people we employ. What matters to us is your passion, commitment and determination to succeed and being able to demonstrate you share our values and those of the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be able to demonstrate how you have worked effectively in a multi-disciplinary team, show your commitment to personal development and if experienced how you have supported a team to succeed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will repay your commitment with opportunities for training and personal development, as well as offering you enough time to enjoy the incredible lifestyle on offer in Devon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be based on the Wonford House site in Exeter where the units are located:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Haldon has 12 beds and a team dedicated to providing the best possible outcomes for people with severe eating disorders. They undertake regular training to ensure that the highest standards are maintained and have the Quality Network for Eating Disorders (QED) accreditation from The Royal College of Psychiatrists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jasmine Lodge MBU is a specialist inpatient perinatal mental health unit for mothers and babies from 32 weeks of pregnancy up to one year after birth. Opened in May 2020, it is a brand new unit with capacity for eight mums and their babies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and you’ll become part of an award-winning organisation that is passionate about mental health and learning disability. One that cares about the people it supports and one that also cares about its staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re genuinely committed to working together and involving the people who use our services, their families and carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days (minimum) annual leave + bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to career development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preceptorship scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Range of leadership development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
